WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:02.007
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:05.630 --> 00:08.731
[Hiccup]
<i>This is New Berk at Snoggletog,</i>

00:08.733 --> 00:10.732
<i>the greatest time of the year.</i>

00:10.734 --> 00:13.735
- <i>The lights, the hunting songs...</i>
- [vocalizing]

00:13.737 --> 00:15.469
<i>...the holiday shopping...</i>

00:15.471 --> 00:16.704
- [man] Oh.
- [woman] Uh-huh.

00:16.706 --> 00:19.707
- Cheers!
- <i>...the Yak-nog shooters.</i>

00:19.709 --> 00:21.307
- 'Nother round!
- Make mine a double!

00:21.309 --> 00:23.711
<i>The only thing missing...
was dragons.</i>

00:23.713 --> 00:25.779
[whimpers]

00:25.781 --> 00:29.549
<i>It's been ten years since Vikings
and dragons agreed to live apart.</i>

00:29.551 --> 00:33.285
<i>But that doesn't mean we've
forgotten our flying friends.</i>

00:33.287 --> 00:35.487
And the best part
of it all, Nuffink,

00:35.489 --> 00:37.388
- was on Snoggletog Eve...
- [Nuffink] Yeah?

00:37.390 --> 00:40.025
- ...I'd make Toothless his favorite meal.
- What was it?

00:40.027 --> 00:42.593
- Lake trout with a side of sea trout...
- Yeah. Yeah.

00:42.595 --> 00:45.863
- ...on a bed of brook trout.
- We all like trout.

00:45.865 --> 00:49.366
And even though he's gone,
I still make it for him.

00:49.368 --> 00:51.501
A lot of families
do stuff like this.

00:51.503 --> 00:54.338
It keeps our loved ones in our
hearts, even though they're far away.

00:56.340 --> 00:58.841
- So, want to help me catch some fish?
- Good on ya!

00:58.843 --> 01:00.642
We're gonna
feed Toothless!

01:00.644 --> 01:02.377
I don't need
a fishing pole, Dad!

01:02.379 --> 01:04.479
I'll just butt the wee
fishes with me own wee head!

01:04.480 --> 01:06.481
- Ow!
- [sighs]

01:06.483 --> 01:08.783
- Ow! Ow!
- [Hiccup] Come on, Nuffink. Let's get Toothless a snack.

01:08.785 --> 01:10.684
[laughs]

01:10.686 --> 01:14.487
[Hiccup] <i>We were excited about
making a traditional dragon feast.</i>

01:14.489 --> 01:15.825
<i>And then it hit me.</i>
[grunts]

01:19.627 --> 01:21.661
<i>Not everyone was on board.</i>

01:21.663 --> 01:23.528
[giggles]
Yes! It worked!

01:23.530 --> 01:25.497
Zephyr,
what are you doing?

01:25.499 --> 01:28.500
Testing my dragon
defense system.

01:28.502 --> 01:31.635
You and all the grown-ups in New
Berk are leaving them snacks.

01:31.637 --> 01:34.839
- What if one shows up?
- That would be great. We love dragons.

01:34.841 --> 01:36.907
Why?
They're monsters.

01:36.909 --> 01:42.414
[voices screaming]

01:43.081 --> 01:44.480
- Oh.
- Uh...

01:44.482 --> 01:46.782
I found this in the attic.
It was Grandpa's.

01:46.784 --> 01:49.518
How come you never told us
the truth about dragons?

01:49.520 --> 01:51.653
But we did.
Dragons are wonderful.

01:51.655 --> 01:52.755
They're our friends.

01:52.757 --> 01:55.356
Tell me this.
Are they giant?

01:55.358 --> 01:57.558
- Well, yeah.
- Razor-sharp teeth?

01:57.560 --> 01:59.392
- Breathe fire?
- I suppose so.

01:59.394 --> 02:00.560
- Claws?
- That'd be yes.

02:00.562 --> 02:03.663
- What happened to your leg?
- Oh. Oh. Uh...

02:03.665 --> 02:05.364
That's what I thought.

02:05.366 --> 02:08.101
Maybe we don't leave fish snacks
around to attract them.

02:08.103 --> 02:10.803
'Cause you know who doesn't
want to be dragon dessert?

02:10.805 --> 02:12.505
Me!

02:12.507 --> 02:15.774
Nuffink, do you want to be
dessert for a dragon?

02:15.776 --> 02:18.343
Hmm.
Methinks I don't.

02:18.345 --> 02:20.447
Let's kill
the dragons!

02:20.881 --> 02:23.413
How did this
happen?

02:23.415 --> 02:27.417
Our ancestors were terrified of
dragons because they didn't know them.

02:27.419 --> 02:30.419
Astrid, we cannot let our
kids go down that road.

02:30.421 --> 02:33.856
Hmm. Remember when we were
kids back in Old Berk,

02:33.858 --> 02:36.358
- how we used to put on a pageant at Snoggletog?
- [grunting]

02:36.360 --> 02:37.860
Oh, yeah.
Those were fun.

02:37.862 --> 02:40.428
What if we brought
the pageant back?

02:40.430 --> 02:44.132
We showed the children of New Berk
how humans and dragons became friends?

02:44.134 --> 02:45.800
- [Nuffink] Bigger!
- That's a great idea.

02:45.802 --> 02:48.569
But we've only got
four days until Snoggletog.

02:48.571 --> 02:50.805
Three if you don't count
Black Plague Friday.

02:50.807 --> 02:52.840
Yeah,
nothing gets done.

02:52.842 --> 02:54.941
Everybody's just
shopping and coughing.

02:54.943 --> 02:56.576
- [Zephyr] More spikes.
- [pounding]

02:56.578 --> 02:59.547
I think we can do this.
Let's talk to Gobber.

02:59.915 --> 03:01.613
[growls]

03:01.615 --> 03:03.484
- [grunts]
- [giggles]

03:04.518 --> 03:05.717
You got me!

03:05.719 --> 03:07.587
Kid can take a hit.

03:08.555 --> 03:09.720
[sighs]

03:09.722 --> 03:12.824
- Hey. Are you okay?
- Yeah. Yeah.

03:12.826 --> 03:17.561
It's just, all this talk of
dragons kind of makes me miss him.

03:17.563 --> 03:19.598
It's hard at the
holidays, you know.

03:20.833 --> 03:23.334
Wonder if Toothless
ever misses me.

